	                    Robert Greens to be rehoused in Midlothian


	                    <span id="Template_ctl08_lblMessage"><font color="Red"></font></span>

	                </h1>
                	
<p class="MsoNormal">As part of its legal responsibility to manage
sex offenders following release from prison, MAPPA partners have
arranged for Robert Greens to be housed in Midlothian.<br />
<br />
Public protection and safety are paramount in all decisions made
regarding the management of sex offenders within communities and
all partners have given this matter very careful
consideration.<br />
<br />
Robert Greens is from Midlothian and his management is therefore
the statutory responsibility of Midlothian Council.&nbsp; To do
this effectively we work closely with our partner agencies in line
with MAPPA (MAPPA stands for Multi-Agency Public Protection
Arrangements).<br />
<br />
The clear and consistent advice from experts is that the provision
of stable accommodation and effective monitoring make a key
contribution to minimising the risks sex offenders under MAPPA may
pose.<br />
<br />
Robert Greens has been at several addresses since his release and
this is considered the most stable considering the
circumstances.&nbsp; This arrangement allows partners to maximise
public protection.<br />
<br />
Midlothian is Robert Greens' permanent home.<br />
<br />
Detective Superintendent Alan Crawford, Head of Public Protection
of Lothian &amp; Borders Police and Chair of the Multi Agency
Public Protection Panel, said on behalf of the responsible
authorities (Police, Local Authority, and Health):<br />
<br />
"The agencies responsible for the management of sex offenders in
the local community under MAPPA (Multi Agency Public Protection
Arrangements) can confirm that Robert Greens has been rehoused in
Midlothian.<br />
<br />
"We want to assure the public that their safety is paramount and
robust procedures are in place to manage Robert Greens' return to
the community.<br />
<br />
"We fully understand the concerns of the public and hope that
by&nbsp; providing information and explaining the measures in place
to help protect them, we can allay some of these concerns.&nbsp;
This decision has been taken to meet the exceptionally high level
of interest from the public and media in this specific
individual.<br />
<br />
"Robert Greens is from Midlothian and as such local agencies have
the responsibility by law to manage him on his release from
prison.&nbsp; Extensive research and reviews by experts have shown
clearly that provision of stable housing, access to support
networks and effective monitoring are key ways to minimise the
risks posed by sex offenders.<br />
<br />
"Decisions regarding changes to Robert Greens' management are made
after careful consideration of the detailed risk assessments by
those involved in MAPPA which includes experts and professionals
from the local authority, the police and health.<br />
<br />
"Robert Greens is subject to monitoring and is electronically
tagged which restricts his movements&nbsp; We will not be releasing
specific information regarding these arrangements."<br />
<br />
Further information on MAPPA, with answers to potential questions
is available at:</p>
